$0.50 EPS Expected for ARRIS International plc (ARRS); Disciplined Growth Investors Has Raised Its Mercury Sys Com (MRCY) Holding


					
						July 21, 2017 - By Nellie Frank


Disciplined Growth Investors Inc increased Mercury Sys Inc Com (MRCY) stake by 6.07% reported in 2016Q4 SEC filing. Disciplined Growth Investors Inc acquired 13,175 shares as Mercury Sys Inc Com (MRCY)’s stock rose 3.33%. The Disciplined Growth Investors Inc holds 230,275 shares with $6.96M value, up from 217,100 last quarter. Mercury Sys Inc Com now has $2.12B valuation. The stock rose 0.34% or $0.15 reaching $44.21 per share. About 67,339 shares traded. Mercury Systems Inc (NASDAQ:MRCY) has risen 91.74% since July 21, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 75.04% the S&P500.







 Analysts expect ARRIS International plc (NASDAQ:ARRS) to report $0.50 EPS on August, 2 after the close.They anticipate $0.31 EPS change or 38.27% from last quarter’s $0.81 EPS. ARRS’s profit would be $94.55M giving it 14.12 P/E if the $0.50 EPS is correct. After having $0.33 EPS previously, ARRIS International plc’s analysts see 51.52% EPS growth. About 205,337 shares traded. ARRIS International plc (NASDAQ:ARRS) has risen 22.70% since July 21, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 6.00% the S&P500.
