Alonzo Mancillas |
Sábado, Julio 15, 2017







News headlines about ARRIS International PLC (NASDAQ:ARRS) have been trending somewhat positive this week, according to Accern Sentiment. CNA Financial Corp's holdings in ARRIS International PLC were worth $601,000 at the end of the most recent reporting period.A number of other hedge funds and other institutional investors have also added to or reduced their stakes in the stock. Janus Capital Management LLC acquired a new position in shares of ARRIS International PLC during the fourth quarter worth $208,000. Tyers Asset Management LLC now owns 5,792 shares of the communications equipment provider's stock valued at $153,000 after buying an additional 400 shares during the last quarter. Ameriprise Financial Inc. raised its position in ARRIS International PLC by 60.0% in the first quarter. World Asset Management Inc now owns 12,159 shares of the communications equipment provider's stock valued at $322,000 after buying an additional 564 shares during the last quarter. Strs Ohio raised its position in ARRIS International PLC by 95.0% in the first quarter. The institutional investor bought 43,200 shares of the communications equipment provider's stock, valued at approximately $1,210,000. Tyers Asset Management LLC boosted its stake in shares of ARRIS International PLC by 7.4% in the first quarter. Neuberger Berman Group LLC now owns 2,023,368 shares of the communications equipment provider's stock valued at $53,518,000 after buying an additional 24,743 shares during the period. Capstone Asset Management Co. increased its stake in ARRIS International PLC by 0.3% in the second quarter. The hedge funds in our partner's database now own: 557,538 shares, up from 487,535 shares in 2016Q3. The stock of ARRIS International plc (NASDAQ:ARRS) earned "Sell" rating by Zacks on Monday, September 21. About 291,921 shares traded. The company has a 50 day moving average of $28.36 and a 200 day moving average of $28.00. RBC Capital Markets maintained the stock with "Outperform" rating in Thursday, July 30 report. Baxter Bros Incorporated invested 1.65% of its portfolio in ARRIS International plc (NASDAQ:ARRS). Finally, TheStreet lowered ARRIS International PLC from a "b-" rating to a "c" rating in a research note on Wednesday, May 3rd. The communications equipment provider reported $0.33 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, topping analysts' consensus estimates of $0.32 by $0.01. ARRIS International PLC had a return on equity of 15.77% and a net margin of 2.69%. The company had revenue of $1.48 billion for the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $1.47 billion. On average, equities research analysts expect that ARRIS International PLC will post $2.51 earnings per share for the current fiscal year.
